3ï¸âƒ£ Actual Tools (instead of shapes)
Replace a-box, a-cylinder, etc. with 3D models (.glb / .gltf).
You can find free models here:
Sketchfab
Poly Haven
Google Poly Archive (via Poly Pizza)
<a-asset-item id="hammerModel" src="hammer.glb"></a-asset-item>
<a-entity gltf-model="#hammerModel" position="-2 1 -4" scale="0.5 0.5 0.5"></a-entity>
ğŸ“ Notes:
Put models inside <a-assets> for efficiency.
Adjust scale so they fit your table.

4ï¸âƒ£ Cursor â†’ Replace Dot with Hand
A-Frame lets you use your own cursor image (e.g., a hand PNG).
<!-- Camera + custom cursor -->
<a-entity camera look-controls>
  <a-cursor 
    material="src: url(hand.png); transparent: true;" 
    scale="0.1 0.1 0.1">
  </a-cursor>
</a-entity>
ğŸ“ Notes:
Replace hand.png with your own small image of a hand (transparent background works best).
scale controls the cursor size.
If youâ€™re targeting VR controllers (like Oculus) â†’ A-Frame has a built-in hand-controls:
<a-entity hand-controls="hand: left"></a-entity>
<a-entity hand-controls="hand: right"></a-entity>

5ï¸âƒ£ Lighting (to make it realistic)
